<paragraph blockId="12.[178,1086,561,1259]" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
R e m a r k s: The species was long-time known as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jansson" authorityYear="1922" box="[739,851,562,583]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[739,851,562,583]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">C. nitidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
FABRICIUS, 1775 (see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="BERLAND L. &amp; F. BERNARD" bookContentInfo="145 pp." box="[221,509,591,613]" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" refId="ref9520" refString="BERLAND L. &amp; F. BERNARD (1938): Hymenopt eres vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae, Trigonalidae). 2 In: Faune de France. Vol. 34. Paul Lechevalier, Paris, pp. i ‾ vii + 145 pp." title="Hymenopt eres vespiformes. III. (Cleptidae, Chrysidae, Trigonalidae)" type="book" volumeTitle="Faune de France. Vol. 34" year="1938">BERLAND &amp; BERNARD 1938</bibRefCitation>
); the latter was subsequently recognized as an American species, not occurring in the Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation author="LINSENMAIER" box="[621,826,620,642]" firstAuthor="LINSENMAIER" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="1 - 232" refId="ref10318" refString="LINSENMAIER W. (1959): Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der europaischen Spezies. 2 Mitteilungen der S chweizer Entomologischen Gesellschaft 32 (1): 1 - 232." type="journal article" year="1959">LINSENMAIER 1959</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<bibRefCitation author="KIMSEY L. S. &amp; R. M. BOHART" bookContentInfo="652 pp." journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" refId="ref10071" refString="KIMSEY L. S. &amp; R. M. BOHART (1991) [1990]: The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. 2 Oxford University Press, New York, I-IX, 652 pp." title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World" type="book" year="1991">KIMSEY &amp; BOHART (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="TARBINSKY" box="[314,516,649,671]" firstAuthor="TARBINSKY" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="193 - 204" refId="ref12038" refString="TARBINSKY Yu. S. (2000): The golden wasp genus Chrysis [gr. ignita] (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) in Tien Shan and adjacent territories. 2 Tethys En tomological Research 2: 193 - 204. [In Russian with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="2000">TARBINSKY (2000)</bibRefCitation>
it is reported under the name 
<emphasis box="[888,1085,650,672]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName box="[888,965,650,671]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysis</taxonomicName>
purpurata
</emphasis>
FABRICIUS, 1787, since 
<bibRefCitation author="KIMSEY" box="[444,666,679,701]" firstAuthor="KIMSEY" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" refId="ref10039" refString="KIMSEY L. S. (1988): The identity of three Fabrician Chrysidid species (Hymenoptera)." type="book" year="1988">KIMSEY (1988: 272)</bibRefCitation>
wrongly designated one specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1791" box="[178,296,709,731]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iris">
<emphasis box="[178,296,709,731]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Chrysis iris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Fabricius̕ collection as 
<typeStatus box="[637,730,708,730]" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[764,897,709,731]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">C. purpurata</emphasis>
. This action made 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1791" box="[178,302,738,760]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iris">
<emphasis box="[178,302,738,760]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Chrysis iris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="CHRIST" box="[314,459,737,759]" firstAuthor="CHRIST" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" refId="ref9841" refString="CHRIST J. L. (1791): Naturgeschichte, Klassification und Nomenclatur der Insekten vom Bienen, Wespen und Ameisengeschlecht: als der funften Klasse funfte Ordnung des Linneischen Natursystems von den Insekten, Hymenoptera: mit hautigen Flugeln. Hermannischer Buchhandlung, Frankfurt am Main, 535 pp. + 60 pls." type="book" year="1791">CHRIST, 1791</bibRefCitation>
a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[707,846,739,760]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">C. purpurata</emphasis>
FABRICIUS, 1787 and 
<emphasis box="[178,286,768,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Euchroeus</emphasis>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[510,587,768,789]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[510,587,768,789]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Chrysis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAEUS" box="[594,762,766,788]" firstAuthor="LINNAEUS" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" refId="ref10212" refString="LINNAEUS C. (1761): Fauna Svecica sistens Animalia Sveciae Regni: Mammalia, Aves, Amphibia, Pisces, Insecta, Vermes. Distributa per Classes et Ordines, enera et Species, cum Differentiis, Specierum, Synonymis, Auctorum, Nominibus Incolarum, Locis natalium, Descriptionibus Insectorum. Editio Altera, Auctior. 2 Laurentius Salvius, Stockholmiae, 578 pp. + 2 pls." type="book" year="1761">LINNAEUS, 1761</bibRefCitation>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PAVESI M &amp; F. STRUMIA" box="[777,1039,767,789]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Zoologial Nomenclature" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="26 - 30" part="54" refId="ref10819" refString="PAVESI M. &amp; F. STRUMIA (1997): Case 2988. Euchroeus LATREILLE, 1809 and Chrysis purpurata FABRICIUS, 1787 (currently E. purpuratus) (Insecta, Hymenoptera): proposed conservation of usage; and Chrysis gloriosa FABRICIUS, 1793: proposed suppression of the specific name. Bulletin of Zoologial Nomenclature 54 (1): 26 - 30." title="Case 2988. Euchroeus LATREILLE, 1809 and Chrysis purpurata FABRICIUS, 1787 (currently E. purpuratus) (Insecta, Hymenoptera): proposed conservation of usage; and Chrysis gloriosa FABRICIUS, 1793: proposed suppression of the specific name" type="journal article" year="1997">PAVESI &amp; STRUMIA 1997</bibRefCitation>
). As a consequence, the name of the genus 
<emphasis box="[571,679,797,818]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Euchroeus</emphasis>
LATREILLE, 1809 (type species 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1085,797,818]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysis</taxonomicName>
purpurata
</emphasis>
FABRICIUS, 1787) became 
<emphasis box="[568,670,827,848]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Brugmoia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="RADOSZKOWSKI" box="[679,910,825,847]" firstAuthor="RADOSZKOWSKI" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref10887" refString="RADOSZKOWSKI O. (1877): Chrysidiformis, Mutillidae et Sphegidae. In: Voyage au Turkestan d ̕ Alexis FEDTSCHENKO 2 Izvestia Imperatorskogo Obshtchestva Lyubitelei Estetvoznania Antropologii i Etnografii (14) 2 (5): 1 - 87 + 8 pls." type="book chapter" year="1877">RADOSZKOWSKI, 1877</bibRefCitation>
(type species 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">B. pellucida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="RADOSZKOWSKI" box="[286,521,855,877]" firstAuthor="RADOSZKOWSKI" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref10887" refString="RADOSZKOWSKI O. (1877): Chrysidiformis, Mutillidae et Sphegidae. In: Voyage au Turkestan d ̕ Alexis FEDTSCHENKO 2 Izvestia Imperatorskogo Obshtchestva Lyubitelei Estetvoznania Antropologii i Etnografii (14) 2 (5): 1 - 87 + 8 pls." type="book chapter" year="1877">RADOSZKOWSKI, 1877</bibRefCitation>
) and the valid species 
<emphasis box="[788,1023,856,877]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Euchroeus purpuratus</emphasis>
auct. became 
<emphasis box="[265,470,885,907]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Brugmoia quadrata</emphasis>
(SHUCKARD, 1837). 
<bibRefCitation author="PAVESI M &amp; F. STRUMIA" box="[694,975,884,906]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Zoologial Nomenclature" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="26 - 30" part="54" refId="ref10819" refString="PAVESI M. &amp; F. STRUMIA (1997): Case 2988. Euchroeus LATREILLE, 1809 and Chrysis purpurata FABRICIUS, 1787 (currently E. purpuratus) (Insecta, Hymenoptera): proposed conservation of usage; and Chrysis gloriosa FABRICIUS, 1793: proposed suppression of the specific name. Bulletin of Zoologial Nomenclature 54 (1): 26 - 30." title="Case 2988. Euchroeus LATREILLE, 1809 and Chrysis purpurata FABRICIUS, 1787 (currently E. purpuratus) (Insecta, Hymenoptera): proposed conservation of usage; and Chrysis gloriosa FABRICIUS, 1793: proposed suppression of the specific name" type="journal article" year="1997">PAVESI &amp; STRUMIA (1997)</bibRefCitation>
asked the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature to set aside, under its Plenary Powers, the 
<typeStatus box="[311,404,942,964]" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation by 
<bibRefCitation author="KIMSEY" box="[578,737,943,965]" firstAuthor="KIMSEY" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" refId="ref10039" refString="KIMSEY L. S. (1988): The identity of three Fabrician Chrysidid species (Hymenoptera)." type="book" year="1988">KIMSEY (1988)</bibRefCitation>
for the nominal species 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1085,944,965]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysis</taxonomicName>
purpurata
</emphasis>
FABRICIUS, 1787; to place on the Official List of Generic Names in Zoology the name 
<emphasis box="[278,386,1002,1023]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Euchroeus</emphasis>
LATREILLE, 1809; to place on the Official Index of Specific Names in Zoology the name 
<emphasis box="[406,509,1032,1053]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">purpurata</emphasis>
FABRICIUS, 1787 as published in the binomen 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1084,1032,1053]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysis</taxonomicName>
purpurata
</emphasis>
. The Commission (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[491,615,1060,1081]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" pagination="194 - 196" refId="ref9979" refString="ICZN (1998): Opinion 1906. Euchroeus LATREILLE, 1809 (Insecta, Hymenoptera): conserved; Chrysis purpurata FABRICIUS, 1787 (currently Euchroeus purpuratus): specific name conserved; and Chrysis gloriosa FABRICIUS, 1793: specific name suppressed. 2 Bulletin of Zoological Nomenclature 55 (3): 194 - 196." type="journal article" year="1998">ICZN 1998</bibRefCitation>
: Opinion 1906) accepted the said proposals, and conserved the name 
<emphasis box="[446,554,1090,1111]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Euchroeus</emphasis>
LATREILLE, 1809 on the Official List of Generic Names in Zoology; conserved the name 
<emphasis box="[623,815,1120,1141]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName box="[623,700,1120,1141]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysis</taxonomicName>
purpurata
</emphasis>
FABRICIUS, 1787 on the Official List of Specific Names in Zoology. According to this Opinion, the generic name 
<emphasis box="[178,279,1179,1200]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Brugmoia</emphasis>
RADOSZKOWSKI has to be considered a synonym of the generic name 
<emphasis box="[178,286,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Euchroeus</emphasis>
LATREILLE, and 
<emphasis box="[470,675,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Brugmoia quadrata</emphasis>
(SHUCKARD) is a synonym of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1084,1208,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysis</taxonomicName>
purpurata
</emphasis>
FABRICIUS. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1791" box="[520,637,1237,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iris">
<emphasis box="[520,637,1237,1259]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="409">Chrysis iris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is to be considered the valid name.
</paragraph>
